<?xml version='1.0' standalone='yes'?>
<?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="index.xsl" ?>
<topic title="Keyboard mapping">
  <style>
    .keyboard {
    text-align: center;
    margin: 24pt;
    }
    
    .keyboard-title {
    font-weight: bold;
    }
    
    .keyboard table {
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
    }

    .keyboard th,td {
    text-align: left;
    }
    
    .keyboard th {
    background: #cfc;
    }

    .keyboard td {
    background: #eee;
    }
  </style>

  <h2>Atari Keys</h2>

  <p>
    When possible, Atari keys are mapped to the host keys that generate the same characters. For instance, Shift+2 on a US English keyboard layout
    generates an @ key press in the emulated system, even though Shift+2 generates a double quote (") on the Atari keyboard. Here are the less
    obvious mappings:
  </p>
  
  <div class="keyboard">
    <table>
      <tr>
        <th>Atari key</th>
        <th>Host key</th>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Start</td>
        <td>F2</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Select</td>
        <td>F3</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Option</td>
        <td>F4</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>System Reset</td>
        <td>F5</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Power (Cold Reset)</td>
        <td>Shift+F5</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Help</td>
        <td>F6</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Break</td>
        <td>Pause</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Shift+&lt; (Clear)</td>
        <td>Shift+Delete</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Shift+&gt; (Insert)</td>
        <td>Insert</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Shift+Backspace (Delete)</td>
        <td>Delete</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Fuji / Invert</td>
        <td>Page Down</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Ctrl+Esc</td>
        <td>Ctrl+\</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Ctrl+Shift+Esc</td>
        <td>Ctrl+Shift+\</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Ctrl+-</td>
        <td>Up Arrow*</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Ctrl+=</td>
        <td>Down Arrow*</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Ctrl++</td>
        <td>Left Arrow*</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Ctrl+*</td>
        <td>Right Arrow*</td>
      </tr>
    </table>
  </div>
  <ul>
    <li>
      The arrow keys can also be typed on the host as Ctrl+Arrow Key. This allows the keyboard arrow keys to be used
      while the arrow keys are already mapped to the joystick.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Host Keys</h2>
  <p>
    These are the mappings from host keys to emulator functions:
  </p>
  <div class="keyboard">
    <table>
      <tr>
        <th>Host key</th>
        <th>Function</th>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Alt+Shift+C</td>
        <td>Copy frame to clipboard</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Alt+Shift+V</td>
        <td>Paste text</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Ctrl+\</td>
        <td>Ctrl+Esc</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Ctrl+Shift+\</td>
        <td>Ctrl+Shift+Esc</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Alt+Enter</td>
        <td>Toggle full-screen mode</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>F1</td>
        <td>Warp speed</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Ctrl+F1</td>
        <td>Toggle filter mode</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>F2</td>
        <td>Start</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>F3</td>
        <td>Select</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>F4</td>
        <td>Option</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>F5</td>
        <td>System Reset</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Shift+F5</td>
        <td>Power (Cold Reset)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>F6</td>
        <td>Help</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>F8</td>
        <td>Run / Break</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>F9</td>
        <td>Toggle Breakpoint</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>F10</td>
        <td>Step Over</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>F11</td>
        <td>Step Into</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Pause</td>
        <td>Break</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Shift+Delete</td>
        <td>Shift+&lt; (Clear)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Insert</td>
        <td>Shift+&gt; (Insert)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Delete</td>
        <td>Shift+Backspace (Delete)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Page Down</td>
        <td>Fuji / Invert</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Up Arrow*</td>
        <td>Ctrl+-</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Down Arrow*</td>
        <td>Ctrl+=</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Left Arrow*</td>
        <td>Ctrl++</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Right Arrow*</td>
        <td>Ctrl+*</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Right Alt (AltGr)</td>
        <td>Release mouse capture</td>
      </tr>
    </table>
  </div>
</topic>